Taiwan Stocks: Chunghwa Telecom, MediaTek Inc., Nanya Technology

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-07-22T06:01:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-22/acer-inc-china-steel-htc-corp-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:30 p.m. close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 48.18, or 0.6 percent, to 8,765.32,
the third day of gains and the highest closing level since July
7. The benchmark rose 2.2 percent in the past five days, the
biggest gain in three weeks.  Chunghwa Telecom Co. (2412 TT) dropped 4.2 percent to
NT$99.60, the lowest close since June 30. The company, Taiwan’s
largest phone operator, was cut to “neutral” from “buy” at
Nomura Holdings Inc. amid valuation concerns.  MediaTek Inc. (2454)  (2454 TT) increased 2.2 percent to NT$277,
the highest close since July 8, after the chip designer
introduced a new chip for smartphones, tablets, portable media
players and gaming devices. Daiwa Securities Capital Markets Co.
reiterated an “outperform” rating for the company today.  Nanya Technology Corp. (2408)  (2408 TT) surged 6.9 percent to
NT$6.66 and  Inotera Memories Inc. (3474)  (3474 TT) jumped 4.6 percent
to NT$7.80. The companies’ shares were “oversold” and
Microsoft Corp. posted better-than-forecast profits, boosting
the outlook for personal computers, said Ben Yeh, an analyst at
KGI Securities Co.  Nanya has dropped 18 percent this month, while Inotera lost
12 percent. The companies make dynamic random-access memory, the
most common chip in computers.  Young Fast Optoelectronics Co. (3622 TT) retreated 3.3
percent to NT$148.50, the lowest close since March 16, 2009.
Samsung Securities Co. cut its share-price estimate to NT$140
from NT$190, saying the company’s second-quarter gross margin
could decline further from a three-year low in the first
quarter. Sharon Ho, a spokeswoman for the company, didn’t
immediately answer calls to her office.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
